steps.instruction:
### Prep
1. Halve the grape tomatoes

### Steps
1. Drain and rinse 3 cans of beans
2. Place in blender with broth; blend until smooth
3. Strain puree through a fine mesh strainer; discard solids (if desired)
4. Pour puree into large stockpot with remaining 1 can of beans (undrained)
5. Place pot on medium heat
6. Stir in oil, coconut milk, salt, pepper, and cloves; bring to a simmer
7. Cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally
8. Cook rice following package instructions
9. Halve tomatoes; remove cilantro leaves from stems
10. Serve soup over rice. Top with sour cream, tomatoes, and cilantro
